Serial 01485 Beacon Coloring Paste

Next to the resplendent colors floating in the void lies a flat tin tube of about 32 cm in length and 3 cm in diameter. The tube is filled with dark gold gel, which absorbs all known colors and turns into that specific shade in the end.

This is a commonly seen emergency item the Nameless carries. Whether in the void of the cosmos or on the ocean of a planet, the Beacon Coloring Paste will always release a line of brilliant colors on the cosmic darkness or on an ocean. It will also adjust its own color contrast and saturation based on the light source and shade of its surroundings.

The bright, visually stimulating colors of the Beacon Coloring Paste allow the Galactic Rescue to easily spot signs written with it. It was invented by a Nameless who possessed great artistic abilities. This Nameless once experienced a flight incident and was trapped in a barren and desolate star system. In the end, with the use of scraps from a White Star fragment, he was able to produce the most magnificent item in the history of search and rescue &mdash; the Beacon Coloring Paste.

There are also cosmic bandits who use the Beacon Coloring Paste to leave graffiti packed with profanity everywhere in the universe out of ill intentions, a rebellious nature, or an inflated ego.


